  "title": "Boutique Manager #82135",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Fine Jewellery Manufacturer & Retailer</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Boutique Manager</strong></li><li>Working Location: Central</li><li>Working Hours: 5-day work week on a rotating roster, including weekends, from Monday to Sunday, 11:00am to 7:00pm</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic + Commission + Performance Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Drive boutique sales performance and achieve monthly, quarterly, and annual targets.</li><li>Deliver a seamless, elevated client journey from first contact to post-sale follow-up.</li><li>Lead clienteling strategies for customers, prospects, and returning clients.</li><li>Grow and manage a High Jewellery client portfolio through personalised relationship building.</li><li>Analyse sales results, client data, and market trends to identify opportunities.</li><li>Oversee daily boutique operations including inventory, after-sales service, visual merchandising, and rostering.</li><li>Ensure effective use of CRM and alignment with Marketing and HQ teams.</li><li>Manage stock levels, replenishment, and operational reporting.</li><li>Ensure full compliance with company policies, SOPs, and security standards.</li><li>Lead, coach, and develop a team of luxury sales professionals.</li><li>Partner with Marketing to deliver exclusive client events and experiences.</li><li>Represent the brand at key client appointments, jewellery presentations, and activations.</li><li>Build strong local market relationships through networking and brand presence</li><li>Perform other duties assigned by management.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>5–7 years’ experience in luxury retail, ideally within fine or high jewellery, including a minimum of 3 years in a boutique leadership role.</li><li>Demonstrated success in driving sales and building long-term relationships with clients.</li><li>Strong knowledge of boutique operations, inventory control, and handling high-value merchandise.</li><li>Background in gemmology, jewellery design, or horology is an advantage; formal gemmological certification preferred.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#82135 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Rachael Lee | EA Reg No.: R2093131</p>",
